President William Ruto on Saturday mourned the death of Trade and Industrialisation CS Moses Kuria's sister Pauline Nyokabi Kuria. In a statement on Twitter, the President prayed to God to grant the family grace to bear the loss. "Our deepest condolences to Moses Kuria for the loss of your dear sister, Pauline Nyokabi Kuria. We grieve with your family and pray that the Lord grants you the grace to bear the loss," he said. Kenyans on Twitter grieved with the CS praying for peace and strength for the family.